---
const PB = [
  {
    t: 'Support & CX transformation',
    q: 'Why do customers need to contact you at all?',
    d: 'Contact-driver taxonomy, root-cause tree, knowledge governance, escalation and decision rights, preventable-contact backlog.',
    dom: 'Operations · CX · content · policy',
  },
  {
    t: 'Digital buying system',
    q: 'What is the journey costing you before the ad spend?',
    d: 'Current and future-state buying journey, friction register, offer hierarchy, checkout certainty, behaviour-trigger rules with margin guardrails.',
    dom: 'Conversion · UI/UX · offer · fulfilment',
  },
  {
    t: 'Operations & workflows',
    q: 'Which work should stop existing?',
    d: 'Process maps, waste and duplication register, decision rights, SOPs and exception rules, capacity model, automation candidates.',
    dom: 'Process · ownership · capacity · control',
  },
  {
    t: 'Growth & market expansion',
    q: 'Is acquisition really the constraint?',
    d: 'Growth-readiness diagnostic, positioning and offer economics, entry pilot, channel sequence, stop and scale criteria.',
    dom: 'Market · economics · channel · risk',
  },
];
---

<section class="section pb" id="playbooks" aria-labelledby="pb-h">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="eyebrow">Transformation playbooks</span>
      <h2 id="pb-h" class="sec-head__q">How I would take a department apart — and what I would put back.</h2>
      <p class="muted">
        Not claims that a company achieved every result shown. Detailed operating methods, with
        every hypothetical scenario visibly labelled as one.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="pb__grid">
      {PB.map((p) => (
        <article class="pb__card">
          <h3 class="pb__t">{p.t}</h3>
          <p class="pb__q">{p.q}</p>
          <p class="pb__d">{p.d}</p>
          <p class="faint pb__dom">{p.dom}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p class="faint pb__note">
      Full playbooks — including the diagnostic models, ranked interventions, deliverables, and
      metrics — are the next build stage. Every scenario in them stays labelled
      <span class="badge badge--illustrative">Illustrative Scenario</span> until a verified case
      replaces it.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .pb__grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: var(--s4); }
  @media (max-width: 860px) { .pb__grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .pb__card {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--s3);
    padding: var(--s5); background: var(--surface-raise);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline); border-radius: var(--r-md);
  }
  .pb__t { font-size: var(--fs-h4); }
  .pb__q { font-family: var(--font-head); font-size: var(--fs-small); font-weight: 600; color: var(--teal-bright); }
  .pb__d { font-size: var(--fs-small); color: var(--text-muted); }
  .pb__dom { margin-top: auto; padding-top: var(--s2); }
  .pb__note { margin-top: var(--s5); max-width: var(--measure); display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.35em; align-items: center; }
</style>
